entries.title: Emu cruelty horror: Outrage after five baby chicks left for dead in Hawke National Park, Yeagarup
entries.description: GRAPHIC IMAGES: The chicks were discovered in various states of trauma with horrific injuries across a dead end road in Hawke National Park at Yeagarup in Western Australia's south-west.

entries.title: Rail workers could receive new pay offer of 9% TODAY in bid to end RMT strikes
entries.description: It is understood train bosses will make a new pay offer of at least 9 per cent over two years to workers for 14 firms. This is up from the current 8 per cent offer.

entries.title: Prince William complained about his father and step-mother 'planting' media stories, Harry claims
entries.description: Prince Harry claims he took a call in April 2019 from William who was 'seething' with rage and believed their father and step-mother had 'planted' a damaging story about he and his family.

entries.title: Tuition fees to be frozen at £9,250 for the next two years
entries.description: Tuition fees will be frozen at £9,250 for the next two years in response to 'cost-of-living pressures'. And the maximum student loans for living costs will rise by 2.8 per cent in 2023/24 in England.

entries.title: Cardinal George Pell death: Daniel Andrews says there will not be a state funeral for Cardinal Pell
entries.description: Responding to questions about whether the Victorian government would host a memorial for the Cardinal, the state Premier made it clear no service would be offered.

entries.title: Karine Jean-Pierre insists Biden is NOT coming for gas stoves
entries.description: White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre insisted Wednesday that President Joe Biden was not coming after Americans' gas stoves.

entries.title: Top Republican demands DOJ appoint a special counsel to investigate Biden's classified documents
entries.description: The Florida congressman also questioned 'who knew' about the documents between their discovery and the Nov. 8 elections and why they were not disclosed during that six-day window.

entries.title: Shocking truth about Anthony Albanese's selfie with Dan Andrews
entries.description: Billionaire trucking boss Lindsay Fox hosted Anthony Albanese and Dan Andrews at his sprawling clifftop mansion in Portsea, near Melbourne.

entries.title: Trouble-hit Ajax tank is finally given all-clear to be pressed into service
entries.description: A £5.5billion armoured vehicle which is already six years late, made troops deaf and could not fire on the move is to enter service.

entries.title: Fury as Prince Harry tries to blame media over confession that he killed 25 Taliban on battlefield
entries.description: During an appearance on US television, Harry said he included the detail of killing 25 Taliban fighters in his controversial memoir Spare to reduce suicides in veteran communities.

entries.title: NSW mosquito virus capable of causing convulsions and lifelong neurological damage
entries.description: The Murray Valley encephalitis (MVE) virus was detected in a mosquito in Menindee, in the far west of NSW.

entries.title: Controversial opinion on mobile speed cameras divides Australia
entries.description: Sneakily-placed speed cameras are possibly the most unpopular form of road rule enforcement among drivers - but one Australian is arguing they're actually good for everyone.

entries.title: Canadian mom-of-three died in agony while waiting nearly SEVEN HOURS for help at emergency room
entries.description: Allison Holthoff, 37, died after waiting seven hours for treatment in Canada. She was left writhing in agony in the ER while nurses brushed her off, and she finally died of cardiac arrest.

entries.title: Gold Coast woman leaves note for driver parked in disability space without a permit
entries.description: A woman struggling with a chronic disability left an incredibly nice note to the driver who parked in her disability space for an entire week - without a permit.

entries.title: Migrants who arrive on cross-Channel dinghies will face 'rapid removal' from UK
entries.description: Channel migrants will face an automatic ban on making asylum claims under tough new immigration measures being drawn up by Suella Braverman, the Daily Mail can reveal.

entries.title: SNP's transgender reforms could rewrite equality laws across UK, think-tank warns
entries.description: Under Ms Sturgeon's 'self-ID' bill passed last month, anyone who legally changed their gender in Scotland would be recognised as the opposite sex in the rest of Britain.
